title: Netflix Subscriber Growth Disappoints in U.S.
text:
Netflix Inc. reported disappointing subscriber growth in the U.S. and saw its profit fall amid higher costs for content and expansion.
Overall, the video company added 3.62 million streaming subscribers in the September quarter, better than the 3.55 million that Netflix projected in July. Netflix said it added more international subscribers... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
